metadata.title: Bell 47
aws::graph::propositions: Bell 47 Aircraft on Static Display in Museums Worldwide
Chilean Air Force Bell 47D-1 with registration H-03 is on static display at the Museo Nacional Aeronáutico y del Espacio in Santiago, Chile.
French Air Force Bell 47G with registration 710 is on static display at the Musée de l'air et de l'espace in Le Bourget, Île-de-France, France.
German Army Agusta-Bell 47G-2 with registration AS+058 is on static display at the Deutsches Museum in Munich, Bavaria, Germany.
Kawasaki-Bell 47D-1 with registration JA7008 is on static display at ANA Safety Education Center near Haneda Airport, Japan.
Kawasaki-Bell 47D-1 with registration JA7008 was one of the first two aircraft of All Nippon Airways.
Kawasaki-Bell 47D-1 with registration JA7008 was once displayed at the Transportation Museum of Japan until its closure in 2006.
Bell 47G-2 with registration AS7201 is on static display at the Malta Aviation Museum in Ta'Qali, Malta.

text:
Chile
H-03 (Chilean Air Force) – Bell 47D-1 on static display at the Museo Nacional Aeronáutico y del Espacio in Santiago.
France
710 (French Air Force) – Bell 47G on static display at the Musée de l’air et de l’espace in Le Bourget, Île-de-France.
Germany
AS+058 (German Army) – Agusta-Bell 47G-2 on static display at the Deutsches Museum in Munich, Bavaria.
Japan
JA7008 – Kawasaki-Bell 47D-1 (one of first two aircraft of All Nippon Airways) on static display at ANA Safety Education Center, nearby Haneda Airport. It was once displayed at  Transportation Museum of Japan until its closure in 2006.
Malta
AS7201 – Bell 47G-2 on static display at the Malta Aviation Museum in Ta'Qali.
